Rating: 3
I find couscous recipes starting with plain couscous dull. I made this with "Near East Whole Wheat Couscous with Garlic and Olive Oil", cooked with equal parts chicken broth and water (may do all broth next time),skipped the saffron, upped the herbs to include 2 scallions, basil and parsley, partially defrosted frozen baby peas and cooked VIA the bowl method (first time I ever cooked this way - it is the way to go for fluffy couscous). Was great!

Rating: 4
This was incredibly simple and delicious, and I used frozen sweetlet peas! I added the saffron to the broth then set it to boil. I measured the couscous into a 4-cup glass measure, then poured the frozen peas on top. I stirred the butter into the boiling broth, then poured it over the peas/couscous to cover completely. By the time the couscous absorbed the water, the peas were perfectly crisp-cooked. I 'fluffed' in the cup while adding the chives, and this turned out perfectly. To save time and mess, I re-used the broth pot to prepare veggies while waiting for the couscous. Yummy!!

