This was very good - I made it with fresh peas and don't think it would be as good with frozen. I like frozen peas a lot, but with something this simple, I think the ingredients are very important. I had no chives, so substituted fresh parsley. I think part of the dish's success lies in the rather large quantity of butter (ok, it's not THAT extravagant, but it's more fat than I usually put in my couscous). A lovely light main dish with a salad, or side dish.

